        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 19 at 4:29PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 428 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from Majestic to near Mouthcard.
Movement was east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Welch, Grundy, Pineville, Hanover, R.d. Bailey Lake, Big Rock,
Gilbert Creek, Paw Paw, Gilbert, Davy, Bradshaw, Iaeger, Panther,
Jolo, Stacy, Hurley, Avondale, Wolf Pen, Baileysville, and Roseann.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

To report severe weather, contact your nearest law enforcement
agency. They will relay your report to the National Weather Service
office in Charleston West Virginia.</instruction>
